      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm seeing some memory growth in our trading engine during stress tests. i think it's a leak in this module. i'm using raw pointers for a high-speed buffer but we keep losing bytes every cycle. can u take a look at this snippet and tell me why the deallocation isn't hitting?\n\n```cpp\nvoid process_order(Order* order) {\n    if (order == nullptr) return;\n    \n    OrderData* data = new OrderData(order->id);\n    // ... some heavy processing logic ...\n    if (order->is_cancelled) {\n        return; // <--- I think the leak is here?\n    }\n    \n    delete data;\n    delete order;\n}\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
